value.value: A neoplastic process that affects the glandular epithelial cells of the cervix.  There is no evidence of invasion.  It is classified as low or high grade.

label.value: Low Grade Cervical Glandular Intraepithelial Neoplasia

value.value: Cervical glandular intraepithelial neoplasia characterized by the presence of mild dysplastic changes.
An odorless, tasteless, poisonous gas, CO, that results from the incomplete combustion of carbon. Inhalation causes central nervous system damage and asphyxiation.
A clear, colorless liquid used as a plasticizer for fabricating flexible materials for many household products. It is also used in cosmetics, insecticides and aspirin.

label.value: High Grade Cervical Glandular Intraepithelial Neoplasia

value.value: Cervical glandular intraepithelial neoplasia characterized by the presence of severe dysplastic changes.

A synthetic psoralen, light-activated DNA and RNA crosslinking agent, with protective activity against pathogens such as bacteria, viruses, protozoa, and leukocytes. Prior to administration amotosalen is added to plasma and platelets, then in vivo this agent penetrates pathogens and targets DNA and RNA. Upon activation by ultraviolet A light, this agent is able to form interstrand DNA and RNA crosslinks and prevents replication. Inactivation of leukocytes can prevent graft versus host disease upon transfusion.
